      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:2:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) إِنَّ أَعْتَى النَّاسِ عَلَى اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ مَنْ قَتَلَ غَيْرَ قَاتِلِهِ وَ مَنْ ضَرَبَ مَنْ لَمْ يَضْرِبْهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘The most trouble-maker of the people to Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic, is the one who killed someone other than his (attempted) killer, and the one who struck someone who did not strike him’."
        ]
      }
    }
